00:41:31.586 --> 00:41:32.850
without government funding.

765
00:41:32.986 --> 00:41:34.954
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

766
00:41:35.089 --> 00:41:37.450
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

767
00:41:37.585 --> 00:41:39.185
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

768
00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:42.060
especially after
the Nixon thing.

769
00:41:42.196 --> 00:41:45.835
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

770
00:41:45.970 --> 00:41:49.165
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

771
00:41:51.271 --> 00:41:54.511
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

772
00:41:55.675 --> 00:41:59.038
This all stops now.

773
00:41:59.173 --> 00:42:00.815
What are you gonna do?

774
00:42:01.818 --> 00:42:06.380
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

775
00:42:09.222 --> 00:42:12.089
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

776
00:42:13.329 --> 00:42:14.993
On everything?

777
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:17.357
What...

778
00:42:17.493 --> 00:42:19.195
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

779
00:42:19.330 --> 00:42:22.166
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

780
00:42:22.301 --> 00:42:25.002
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

781
00:42:25.138 --> 00:42:27.400
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

782
00:42:27.536 --> 00:42:29.307
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

783
00:42:29.442 --> 00:42:31.843
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

784
00:42:31.979 --> 00:42:34.582
this core truth
about the universe.

785
00:42:34.718 --> 00:42:36.850
- It's wrong.
- You can't do that.

786
00:42:38.013 --> 00:42:39.688
Think about...

787
00:42:41.315 --> 00:42:42.756
People will see them as deities.

788
00:42:42.892 --> 00:42:44.787
They'll stop believing in God.

789
00:42:44.923 --> 00:42:46.691
Well. you left the church.

790
00:42:46.826 --> 00:42:48.224
Not because I stopped believing.

791
00:42:48.359 --> 00:42:49.857
because I could no longer say
with certainty

792
00:42:49.993 --> 00:42:51.359
that God is divine.

793
00:42:51.494 --> 00:42:54.571
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

794
00:42:56.331 --> 00:42:57.838
He's how we define ourselves.

795
00:42:57.973 --> 00:43:00.841
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

796
00:43:02.407 --> 00:43:05.176
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

797
00:43:05.311 --> 00:43:08.976
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

798
00:43:09.112 --> 00:43:10.818
People can't handle both.

799
00:43:13.390 --> 00:43:15.057
Of course they can.

800
00:43:15.192 --> 00:43:16.682
No. they can't.

801
00:43:17.685 --> 00:43:19.655
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

802
00:43:20.691 --> 00:43:24.964
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

803
00:43:26.563 --> 00:43:31.036
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

804
00:43:35.270 --> 00:43:37.405
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

805
00:43:49.226 --> 00:43:50.858
No signal.

806
00:43:52.658 --> 00:43:54.420
No signal.

807
00:43:54.556 --> 00:43:56.666
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

808
00:44:26.727 --> 00:44:27.959
Okay.

809
00:44:28.095 --> 00:44:29.289
Unlock the door!

810
00:44:29.424 --> 00:44:30.631
- What?
- Jackson. come on!

811
00:44:30.767 --> 00:44:32.427
Oh. shit. Sorry.

812
00:44:33.601 --> 00:44:35.304
Oh. sorry. sorry.

813
00:44:35.440 --> 00:44:37.839
- Okay.
- Oh. my God.

814
00:44:43.672 --> 00:44:45.174
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

815
00:44:45.309 --> 00:44:46.576
I'm marching you
right back inside.

816
00:44:46.711 --> 00:44:48.246
Hello?

817
00:44:48.381 --> 00:44:50.210
I've been
waiting a very long time

818
00:44:50.345 --> 00:44:52.517
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

819
00:44:52.652 --> 00:44:54.090
Who is this?

820
00:44:54.225 --> 00:44:55.857
A friend.

821
00:44:57.092 --> 00:44:59.789
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

822
00:44:59.925 --> 00:45:01.320
you'd know if I wasn't.

823
00:45:01.455 --> 00:45:02.864
No. I don't... I don't know you

824
00:45:02.999 --> 00:45:04.692
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

825
00:45:04.828 --> 00:45:07.034
Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

826
00:45:07.169 --> 00:45:08.870
- I'm not managing it. I'm not.
- Who-who is that?

827
00:45:09.005 --> 00:45:11.302
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

828
00:45:11.437 --> 00:45:15.404
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

829
00:45:15.539 --> 00:45:17.246
- Let us help you get there.
- Help me how?

830
00:45:17.381 --> 00:45:18.404
What do you mean?

831
00:45:18.539 --> 00:45:19.880
- Is that the FBI?
- Shh!

832
00:45:20.016 --> 00:45:21.043
We want to offer you
our protection.

833
00:45:21.178 --> 00:45:22.542
We held back on reaching out

834
00:45:22.678 --> 00:45:24.615
until after we saw
your weather report.

835
00:45:24.751 --> 00:45:26.084
You held back?

836
00:45:26.220 --> 00:45:27.214
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

837
00:45:27.349 --> 00:45:29.154
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

838
00:45:32.890 --> 00:45:35.765
Who is 873-2626?

839
00:45:37.458 --> 00:45:38.834
Since you know that number.

840
00:45:38.969 --> 00:45:41.232
you must already know
who it belongs to.

841
00:45:43.570 --> 00:45:44.807
Kellner?

842
00:45:45.836 --> 00:45:46.736
Kellner?

843
00:45:46.871 --> 00:45:48.607
All right.

844
00:45:48.742 --> 00:45:50.235
Listen carefully.

845
00:45:50.371 --> 00:45:51.714
You cannot go home.

846
00:45:51.850 --> 00:45:53.111
If you have another direction
in mind.

847
00:45:53.246 --> 00:45:55.311
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

848
00:45:55.447 --> 00:45:57.149
If we can find you by phone.
others can

849
00:45:57.284 --> 00:45:59.017
- find you in the world.
- No. it's too late.

850
00:45:59.152 --> 00:46:00.515
They...
Uh. they already found me.

851
00:46:00.650 --> 00:46:03.249
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

852
00:46:03.384 --> 00:46:04.726
How will you find me?

853
00:46:04.862 --> 00:46:06.085
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

854
00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:07.258
Do it now.

855
00:46:09.066 --> 00:46:11.867
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

856
00:46:13.504 --> 00:46:14.435
Back up over the phone.

857
00:46:14.571 --> 00:46:16.303
- What?
- Back up!

858
00:46:16.438 --> 00:46:18.006
- Come on.
- Okay. I'd like to point out that I'm being

859
00:46:18.142 --> 00:46:20.266
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

860
00:46:20.402 --> 00:46:22.441
and that was a $600 phone.

861
00:46:23.444 --> 00:46:25.343
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

862
00:46:25.478 --> 00:46:26.844
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

863
00:46:26.979 --> 00:46:28.015
- Come on.
- Sorry.

864
00:46:32.550 --> 00:46:34.654
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

865
00:46:34.790 --> 00:46:36.826
- Okay.
- What?

866
00:46:40.594 --> 00:46:41.930
Okay.

867
00:46:43.601 --> 00:46:46.000
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

868
00:46:47.604 --> 00:46:49.366
Keep going. Keep going.

869
00:46:58.646 --> 00:47:00.948
Okay. Okay.

870
00:47:01.084 --> 00:47:04.320
- Okay. let's go. Let's go.
- Uh... wh-where?

871
00:47:04.455 --> 00:47:05.986
- North.
- Why?

872
00:47:06.122 --> 00:47:07.312
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

873
00:47:07.448 --> 00:47:08.991
Oh. my God.

874
00:47:09.126 --> 00:47:10.685
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

875
00:47:10.821 --> 00:47:12.257
- that you never told me about?
- I don't know. Jackson.

876
00:47:12.392 --> 00:47:13.586
- Or what is it?
- You're giving me a headache.

877
00:47:13.722 --> 00:47:14.495
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

878
00:47:14.631 --> 00:47:15.863
I don't know who he is.

879
00:47:15.999 --> 00:47:17.460
I just know
he's someplace north.

880
00:47:17.596 --> 00:47:18.534
That's all I know. okay?

881
00:47:18.669 --> 00:47:20.001
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

882
00:47:22.431 --> 00:47:24.471
- Your hailstorm.
- Wow.

883
00:47:24.606 --> 00:47:25.902
Weather Shimmy?

884
00:47:26.038 --> 00:47:28.306
Just drive. Just drive.

885
00:48:16.825 --> 00:48:19.357
You got Kellner on 2626.

886
00:48:21.064 --> 00:48:22.622
Look at the video
I just sent you.

887
00:48:22.758 --> 00:48:24.131
DANIEL Okay. hold on.

888
00:48:30.606 --> 00:48:32.038
Yeah. So?

889
00:48:32.174 --> 00:48:33.971
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

890
00:48:34.106 --> 00:48:36.435
Her? Why?

891
00:48:36.570 --> 00:48:38.845
Did you not hear her?

892
00:48:38.981 --> 00:48:40.340
Yeah. I heard her.

893
00:48:40.475 --> 00:48:41.784
And you still ask why?

894
00:48:41.920 --> 00:48:43.684
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

895
00:48:43.820 --> 00:48:45.581
That's all she had to say?

896
00:48:47.024 --> 00:48:49.019
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

897
00:48:49.154 --> 00:48:50.415
That's what she said?

898
00:48:50.551 --> 00:48:52.093
You didn't hear it?

899
00:48:53.563 --> 00:48:55.063
We all heard it.

900
00:48:55.199 --> 00:48:57.293
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

901
00:48:57.428 --> 00:48:58.964
Of course it is.

902
00:48:59.100 --> 00:49:00.993
I'm listening to it right now.

903
00:49:01.128 --> 00:49:02.930
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

904
00:49:03.066 --> 00:49:04.932
- We'll get a car to you. Leave tonight.
- Hey. wait.

905
00:49:05.067 --> 00:49:06.603
- Wait a second. Wait a second.
- Do not travel by day.

906
00:49:06.738 --> 00:49:08.042
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

907
00:49:08.177 --> 00:49:09.139
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

908
00:49:09.275 --> 00:49:10.472
Hey. listen to me.

909
00:49:10.608 --> 00:49:11.710
Have you played this
to other people?

910
00:49:11.846 --> 00:49:13.776
Stay with me.

911
00:49:13.911 --> 00:49:16.545
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

912
00:49:16.681 --> 00:49:18.480
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

913
00:49:18.615 --> 00:49:21.023
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

914
00:49:21.158 --> 00:49:23.758
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

915
00:49:23.894 --> 00:49:27.491
There are two of you. Daniel.

916
00:49:27.626 --> 00:49:30.762
There's always been
just the two of you.

917
00:52:26.105 --> 00:52:27.640
Hello. Jane.

918
00:52:27.776 --> 00:52:29.541
Please.

919
00:52:30.912 --> 00:52:32.940
Have a seat.

920
00:52:38.583 --> 00:52:41.152
Where are you right now. Jane?

921
00:52:41.287 --> 00:52:42.983
What is your location?

922
00:52:44.259 --> 00:52:46.591
- I don't know.
- Relax. please.

923
00:52:49.959 --> 00:52:52.498
- Who are you?
- I'll ask the questions.

924
00:52:53.566 --> 00:52:55.336
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

925
00:53:01.504 --> 00:53:02.838
He's outside.

926
00:53:06.478 --> 00:53:08.074
Where were you last night?

927
00:53:17.659 --> 00:53:20.285
- BP's high but holding: 156/94.
- O2's decent at 96.

928
00:53:20.421 --> 00:53:22.295
- but sodium's climbing.
- Heart rate's hot. too... 118.

929
00:53:22.431 --> 00:53:23.493
- Potassium's borderline. too.
- Jane!

930
00:53:23.628 --> 00:53:25.157
- Stand by. Ringer's.
- Jane!

931
00:53:26.133 --> 00:53:27.627
Jane!

932
00:53:27.763 --> 00:53:30.030
Where were you last night?

933
00:53:31.242 --> 00:53:34.171
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

934
00:53:34.307 --> 00:53:36.403
Monastery St. Clare?

935
00:53:36.538 --> 00:53:37.939
Of course.

936
00:53:38.074 --> 00:53:41.041
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

937
00:53:41.176 --> 00:53:43.118
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

938
00:53:43.254 --> 00:53:45.813
and she had a vision
of it instead.

939
00:53:45.949 --> 00:53:48.488
She was in two places at once.
like me.

940
00:53:51.193 --> 00:53:53.227
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

941
00:53:53.362 --> 00:53:55.262
13 miles southeast
of the District.

942
00:53:55.398 --> 00:53:57.860
When you left.
which way did you drive?

943
00:54:01.564 --> 00:54:02.803
I don't know.

944
00:54:02.938 --> 00:54:04.471
Was the sun up?

945
00:54:07.568 --> 00:54:08.936
Yes.

946
00:54:09.072 --> 00:54:11.280
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

947
00:54:14.710 --> 00:54:16.384
It was on the right.

948
00:54:18.515 --> 00:54:19.952
I don't like you.

949
00:54:20.088 --> 00:54:21.856
Not required.

950
00:54:21.991 --> 00:54:23.424
Sun on the right.

951
00:54:23.560 --> 00:54:25.189
Sun on the right...
they're headed due north.

952
00:54:25.325 --> 00:54:26.591
possibly northwest.

953
00:54:26.726 --> 00:54:28.358
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

954
00:54:28.493 --> 00:54:29.892
Interstate not likely.

955
00:54:30.027 --> 00:54:31.560
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

956
00:54:31.695 --> 00:54:34.231
Did you pass a street sign?

957
00:54:34.366 --> 00:54:35.803
Yes.

958
00:54:35.938 --> 00:54:37.632
What did it say?

959
00:54:41.969 --> 00:54:45.105
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

960
00:54:45.240 --> 00:54:47.647
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

961
00:54:47.782 --> 00:54:50.418
I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

962
00:54:50.553 --> 00:54:53.714
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

963
00:54:53.849 --> 00:54:55.648
Try for more details. Jane.

964
00:54:55.784 --> 00:54:57.322
What else did you pass?

965
00:54:59.224 --> 00:55:00.289
A river.

966
00:55:00.424 --> 00:55:01.990
Passed a river.

967
00:55:02.125 --> 00:55:04.190
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

968
00:55:06.434 --> 00:55:08.535
- Yes.
- What did it say?

969
00:55:13.075 --> 00:55:14.637
S-Sykesville.

970
00:55:14.772 --> 00:55:17.478
- Sykesville.
- Sykesville.

971
00:55:18.680 --> 00:55:21.109
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

972
00:55:21.244 --> 00:55:23.909
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

973
00:55:24.045 --> 00:55:26.312
Maintain maximum legal speed.

974
00:55:26.447 --> 00:55:29.256
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

975
00:55:29.391 --> 00:55:30.993
- A few minutes.
- Few minutes.

976
00:55:31.128 --> 00:55:33.026
Did you turn right or left?

977
00:55:33.161 --> 00:55:34.625
- Right.
- Right.

978
00:55:34.761 --> 00:55:37.357
Do you remember
the name of the road?

979
00:55:37.493 --> 00:55:38.728
No.

980
00:55:38.864 --> 00:55:40.798
Do you remember anything
about the road?

981
00:55:49.442 --> 00:55:51.175
It was a dirt road.

982
00:55:51.310 --> 00:55:52.711
Dirt road.

983
00:55:52.846 --> 00:55:54.511
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

984
00:55:54.647 --> 00:55:56.842
outside Sykesville. dead end.

985
00:55:56.977 --> 00:55:58.446
Farmhouse at the end.

986
00:55:58.582 --> 00:55:59.887
And found it.

987
00:56:00.022 --> 00:56:01.319
Ash Hollow Road.

988
00:56:01.454 --> 00:56:03.656
Target is a farmhouse.

989
00:56:10.530 --> 00:56:12.759
You've done very well. Jane.

990
00:56:12.895 --> 00:56:15.435
A service to your country.

991
00:56:15.571 --> 00:56:18.836
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

992
00:56:18.971 --> 00:56:23.003
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

993
00:56:23.139 --> 00:56:25.539
you may need
to stop him yourself

994
00:56:25.674 --> 00:56:27.581
any way you can.

995
00:56:34.149 --> 00:56:36.084
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

996
00:56:36.219 --> 00:56:38.054
Uh. heart rate's dropping...
down to 59.

997
00:56:38.190 --> 00:56:41.094
Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.

998
00:56:45.736 --> 00:56:47.701
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

999
00:56:47.836 --> 00:56:48.763
Let's start bagging.

1000
00:56:48.898 --> 00:56:50.196
Make sure you secure the airway.

1001
00:56:50.331 --> 00:56:52.907
High 80s. Keep going.

1002
00:56:53.042 --> 00:56:54.936
Get away!

1003
00:57:00.345 --> 00:57:02.143
Jane.

1004
00:57:03.180 --> 00:57:06.250
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1005
00:57:06.385 --> 00:57:08.823
It's dangerous.

1006
00:57:08.958 --> 00:57:12.252
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1007
00:57:13.261 --> 00:57:14.494
Yes.

1008
00:57:14.630 --> 00:57:16.731
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1009
00:57:16.867 --> 00:57:19.633
No. No.

1010
00:57:22.635 --> 00:57:25.535
"Father. if you be willing.

1011
00:57:25.671 --> 00:57:28.608
"let this cup pass me by.

1012
00:57:28.743 --> 00:57:31.971
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1013
00:57:32.107 --> 00:57:34.483
And what did Christ say next?

1014
00:57:36.179 --> 00:57:38.553
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1015
00:57:39.590 --> 00:57:43.091
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1016
00:57:43.226 --> 00:57:45.088
and you'll act. Jane.

1017
00:57:45.223 --> 00:57:48.827
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1018
00:57:52.126 --> 00:57:53.832
Now look around the room.

1019
00:57:55.004 --> 00:57:56.395
Slowly.

1020
