01:22:52.701 --> 01:22:54.067
Why there?

1274
01:22:54.202 --> 01:22:55.927
- I have to.
- You don't have to go so...

1275
01:22:56.062 --> 01:22:57.996
- Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
- Uh. you're enjoying this.

1276
01:22:58.132 --> 01:23:00.667
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1277
01:23:00.802 --> 01:23:02.768
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1278
01:23:02.903 --> 01:23:04.403
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1279
01:23:04.538 --> 01:23:05.936
the last few days. you know.

1280
01:23:06.071 --> 01:23:07.809
- How do you know that?
- I just know things.

1281
01:23:07.944 --> 01:23:09.340
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1282
01:23:09.476 --> 01:23:11.380
and now I-I know things.

1283
01:23:11.515 --> 01:23:12.810
Things I don't really
want to know.

1284
01:23:12.945 --> 01:23:14.017
and all the things
I do want to know.

1285
01:23:14.152 --> 01:23:15.483
I don't really know at all.

1286
01:23:15.619 --> 01:23:17.057
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1287
01:23:17.193 --> 01:23:18.651
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1288
01:23:18.786 --> 01:23:20.325
- That must have been so...
- Hey. hey!

1289
01:23:20.460 --> 01:23:22.056
You see what I mean?

1290
01:23:22.192 --> 01:23:24.329
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1291
01:23:24.464 --> 01:23:28.201
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1292
01:23:29.204 --> 01:23:31.862
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1293
01:23:31.997 --> 01:23:33.634
I see the things
that they've lived.

1294
01:23:33.770 --> 01:23:35.741
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1295
01:23:35.876 --> 01:23:37.308
You know. like-like...

1296
01:23:37.443 --> 01:23:38.803
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1297
01:23:38.938 --> 01:23:40.677
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1298
01:23:40.812 --> 01:23:42.314
- "Keep your eyes on the road!"
- Keep your eyes on the road!

1299
01:23:42.449 --> 01:23:43.975
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1300
01:23:44.110 --> 01:23:45.214
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1301
01:23:45.350 --> 01:23:46.846
- You're absolutely right.
- Jane?

1302
01:23:46.981 --> 01:23:49.386
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1303
01:23:49.521 --> 01:23:51.453
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1304
01:23:51.589 --> 01:23:53.022
It was so strong.

1305
01:23:53.158 --> 01:23:54.689
I dropped right in on you

1306
01:23:54.824 --> 01:23:56.394
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1307
01:23:56.530 --> 01:23:58.162
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1308
01:23:58.298 --> 01:23:59.829
How long you been able
to do this?

1309
01:23:59.964 --> 01:24:01.127
Since yesterday.

1310
01:24:01.262 --> 01:24:02.869
Since the bird.

1311
01:24:03.004 --> 01:24:04.462
- What bird?
- This-this bird.

1312
01:24:04.598 --> 01:24:06.140
Flew in through my window.

1313
01:24:06.275 --> 01:24:08.069
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1314
01:24:08.204 --> 01:24:09.170
Was it a cardinal?

1315
01:24:09.305 --> 01:24:10.535
Holy sh... How the...

1316
01:24:10.670 --> 01:24:12.045
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1317
01:24:18.183 --> 01:24:19.548
I was 20. I was in college.

1318
01:24:19.683 --> 01:24:21.447
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1319
01:24:21.582 --> 01:24:22.879
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1320
01:24:23.015 --> 01:24:24.287
You were. but it was
the partying.

1321
01:24:24.422 --> 01:24:25.385
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1322
01:24:25.520 --> 01:24:26.951
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1323
01:24:27.086 --> 01:24:28.357
- Could you please stop?
- Sorry. I'm stopping.

1324
01:24:28.493 --> 01:24:29.620
- I was 20. I was in college.
- Yes.

1325
01:24:29.755 --> 01:24:32.363
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1326
01:24:32.499 --> 01:24:34.726
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1327
01:24:34.861 --> 01:24:36.365
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1328
01:24:36.501 --> 01:24:37.795
- It was a cardinal.
- In the window.

1329
01:24:37.931 --> 01:24:39.738
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1330
01:24:39.874 --> 01:24:41.339
everything just changed.

1331
01:24:41.474 --> 01:24:43.775
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1332
01:24:43.911 --> 01:24:45.509
I could see it all.

1333
01:24:45.644 --> 01:24:47.407
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1334
01:24:47.543 --> 01:24:48.946
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1335
01:24:49.082 --> 01:24:50.580
Exactly. Solved equations

1336
01:24:50.715 --> 01:24:52.119
- without even thinking...
- And you could read

1337
01:24:52.254 --> 01:24:53.348
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1338
01:24:53.483 --> 01:24:54.512
- like it was nothing.
- Yeah.

1339
01:24:54.648 --> 01:24:55.621
How do you know all this?

1340
01:24:55.756 --> 01:24:57.283
I don't. You do.

1341
01:24:57.418 --> 01:24:58.549
God. you hated it.

1342
01:24:58.685 --> 01:25:00.354
- It was a curse.
- Yeah.

1343
01:25:00.490 --> 01:25:02.186
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1344
01:25:02.322 --> 01:25:03.955
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1345
01:25:04.091 --> 01:25:05.632
to be around people.

1346
01:25:05.768 --> 01:25:07.365
Until you met Jane.

1347
01:25:10.898 --> 01:25:12.467
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1348
01:25:12.603 --> 01:25:14.172
- What?
- That's what you said on TV.

1349
01:25:14.307 --> 01:25:15.774
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1350
01:25:15.910 --> 01:25:17.171
I understood every word.

1351
01:25:17.307 --> 01:25:18.979
What happened to us?

1352
01:25:19.115 --> 01:25:20.981
Oh. my God.

1353
01:25:23.212 --> 01:25:24.481
Who is it?!

1354
01:25:27.150 --> 01:25:28.312
Boyd. stop!

1355
01:25:28.447 --> 01:25:29.585
Boyd!

1356
01:25:38.831 --> 01:25:39.859
Shit.

1357
01:25:40.969 --> 01:25:42.531
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1358
01:25:42.666 --> 01:25:44.501
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1359
01:25:48.602 --> 01:25:50.474
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1360
01:25:52.640 --> 01:25:53.774
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1361
01:25:56.216 --> 01:25:57.778
He's backing up! Get out now!

1362
01:26:11.499 --> 01:26:13.266
All right. all right!

1363
01:26:21.810 --> 01:26:23.243
Get to the ladder!

1364
01:26:29.217 --> 01:26:31.146
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1365
01:26:31.281 --> 01:26:32.580
Okay.

1366
01:27:08.482 --> 01:27:10.482
Go! Jump!

1367
01:27:23.398 --> 01:27:25.096
You got to jump!

1368
01:27:26.071 --> 01:27:27.571
Jump! Now!

1369
01:28:02.206 --> 01:28:03.607
Oh. my God.

1370
01:28:11.747 --> 01:28:14.486
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1371
01:28:15.450 --> 01:28:16.785
I can't breathe.

1372
01:28:18.218 --> 01:28:20.351
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I can't breathe.

1373
01:28:20.487 --> 01:28:22.021
- I think you're having a panic attack.
- Oh. my God.

1374
01:28:22.156 --> 01:28:24.255
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1375
01:28:24.391 --> 01:28:26.133
- It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
- My hands.

1376
01:28:26.268 --> 01:28:27.963
- We're okay.
- It's like my dad.

1377
01:28:28.099 --> 01:28:29.534
- It's like my dad. My hands.
- No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1378
01:28:29.670 --> 01:28:31.501
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1379
01:28:31.637 --> 01:28:32.862
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1380
01:28:32.998 --> 01:28:34.540
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1381
01:28:34.675 --> 01:28:36.440
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1382
01:28:36.575 --> 01:28:38.037
- I can't control it.
- You can.

1383
01:28:38.172 --> 01:28:40.813
Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1384
01:28:40.949 --> 01:28:43.644
- I didn't want to be around him anymore.
- No. no. no. Stop.

1385
01:28:43.779 --> 01:28:45.515
- I want this gone!
- Okay.

1386
01:28:45.651 --> 01:28:48.379
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1387
01:28:48.515 --> 01:28:51.115
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1388
01:28:51.251 --> 01:28:53.090
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1389
01:28:53.226 --> 01:28:54.359
Give me your hands.

1390
01:28:54.494 --> 01:28:55.690
- Okay. look at me.
- No. no. no.

1391
01:28:55.826 --> 01:28:57.121
- Look at me.
- I-I'm gonna see things.

1392
01:28:57.256 --> 01:28:58.862
- I'm gonna see things. Please.
- Okay.

1393
01:28:58.997 --> 01:28:59.922
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1394
01:29:01.496 --> 01:29:03.101
That's it. Okay.

1395
01:29:03.236 --> 01:29:05.167
I can't feel my hands.

1396
01:29:05.302 --> 01:29:07.097
Okay. Okay.

1397
01:29:07.233 --> 01:29:08.938
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1398
01:29:09.074 --> 01:29:10.670
Come on. Put your hands there.

1399
01:29:10.805 --> 01:29:12.670
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1400
01:29:12.806 --> 01:29:14.374
I'm here. I'm here.

1401
01:29:14.509 --> 01:29:15.938
We're here.

1402
01:29:16.074 --> 01:29:17.615
- We're okay.
- Okay.

1403
01:29:18.781 --> 01:29:20.182
- We're okay.
- We're okay.

1404
01:29:20.317 --> 01:29:22.418
We're okay.

1405
01:29:22.553 --> 01:29:25.256
We're okay now. You're okay.

1406
01:29:29.623 --> 01:29:31.665
We're okay.

1407
01:29:31.800 --> 01:29:33.065
Okay.

1408
01:29:37.796 --> 01:29:39.571
Thank you.

1409
01:29:42.635 --> 01:29:44.935
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1410
01:29:45.070 --> 01:29:46.345
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1411
01:29:46.480 --> 01:29:48.415
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1412
01:29:51.149 --> 01:29:53.209
H-Hugo?

1413
01:29:53.345 --> 01:29:54.746
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1414
01:29:54.881 --> 01:29:56.247
for a minute. please?

1415
01:29:56.382 --> 01:29:59.186
- Now. please! Out!
- Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1416
01:30:05.530 --> 01:30:07.159
Hello. Hugo.

1417
01:30:12.799 --> 01:30:14.939
Noah. please.

1418
01:30:15.975 --> 01:30:17.868
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1419
01:30:18.003 --> 01:30:19.875
It's not a magic wand.

1420
01:30:20.010 --> 01:30:21.743
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1421
01:30:21.879 --> 01:30:24.747
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1422
01:30:24.883 --> 01:30:29.388
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1423
01:30:29.523 --> 01:30:31.383
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1424
01:30:31.519 --> 01:30:33.726
Yes.

1425
01:30:33.862 --> 01:30:35.627
He was.

1426
01:30:37.422 --> 01:30:41.501
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1427
01:30:42.765 --> 01:30:44.599
Not in any way you'd understand.

1428
01:30:44.734 --> 01:30:46.298
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1429
01:30:46.434 --> 01:30:48.904
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1430
01:30:49.039 --> 01:30:51.408
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1431
01:30:51.543 --> 01:30:52.904
No. don't condescend to me.

1432
01:30:53.039 --> 01:30:54.481
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1433
01:30:54.616 --> 01:30:56.576
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1434
01:30:56.711 --> 01:30:58.146
From your friends?

1435
01:30:58.282 --> 01:30:59.883
Yes.

1436
01:31:00.019 --> 01:31:02.817
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1437
01:31:02.953 --> 01:31:05.459
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1438
01:31:05.594 --> 01:31:09.561
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1439
01:31:09.696 --> 01:31:11.758
Our rejection
of this understanding

1440
01:31:11.893 --> 01:31:14.097
is leading us to our extinction.

1441
01:31:15.100 --> 01:31:18.131
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1442
01:31:20.107 --> 01:31:21.634
Five years ago.

1443
01:31:21.770 --> 01:31:23.675
That was you. wasn't it?

1444
01:31:25.408 --> 01:31:26.678
Yes.

1445
01:31:27.945 --> 01:31:30.779
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1446
01:31:30.914 --> 01:31:33.113
how could you lie to me
for five years

1447
01:31:33.248 --> 01:31:34.852
every time you walked
through the door?

1448
01:31:34.987 --> 01:31:37.689
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1449
01:31:39.661 --> 01:31:42.822
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1450
01:31:42.957 --> 01:31:45.323
Around the time you lost yours.

1451
01:31:47.762 --> 01:31:49.360
When you lost her.

1452
01:31:53.698 --> 01:31:56.340
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1453
01:31:56.475 --> 01:31:57.704
Because you shut down.

1454
01:31:57.840 --> 01:31:59.269
Do not presume to know me.

1455
01:31:59.405 --> 01:32:00.675
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1456
01:32:00.811 --> 01:32:02.347
to need-to-know. including me.

1457
01:32:02.482 --> 01:32:03.645
Because you were very clear.

1458
01:32:03.780 --> 01:32:05.144
All you needed to know was them.

1459
01:32:05.279 --> 01:32:07.481
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1460
01:32:07.617 --> 01:32:10.156
They will be.

1461
01:32:10.291 --> 01:32:12.348
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1462
01:32:12.484 --> 01:32:14.194
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1463
01:32:14.329 --> 01:32:16.288
You don't need to fear them.

1464
01:32:17.296 --> 01:32:19.194
I fear us.

1465
01:32:19.330 --> 01:32:22.362
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1466
01:32:22.498 --> 01:32:26.562
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1467
01:32:26.698 --> 01:32:28.404
That truth will upend
all established order

1468
01:32:28.540 --> 01:32:29.839
across the entire world.

1469
01:32:29.974 --> 01:32:32.370
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1470
01:32:32.505 --> 01:32:36.714
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1471
01:32:36.849 --> 01:32:39.175
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1472
01:32:39.310 --> 01:32:40.585
Your own wealth and power...

1473
01:32:40.720 --> 01:32:42.384
that's all
you've been protecting.

1474
01:32:42.519 --> 01:32:45.285
Noah. Noah.

1475
01:32:45.420 --> 01:32:47.559
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1476
01:32:47.694 --> 01:32:50.927
and an equal need
to be believed.

1477
01:32:51.062 --> 01:32:53.199
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1478
01:32:53.335 --> 01:32:54.932
You've infantilized anyone

1479
01:32:55.068 --> 01:32:57.636
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1480
01:32:57.771 --> 01:33:00.573
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1481
01:33:00.709 --> 01:33:03.267
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1482
01:33:03.403 --> 01:33:05.102
and overridden them
for the crime

1483
01:33:05.237 --> 01:33:07.207
of simply being astonished.

1484
01:33:07.342 --> 01:33:10.041
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1485
01:33:10.176 --> 01:33:11.950
the chance to believe them. too.

1486
01:33:12.085 --> 01:33:14.619
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1487
01:33:14.755 --> 01:33:16.388
telling others
of their experiences.

1488
01:33:16.523 --> 01:33:18.786
They are starved for the truth.

1489
01:33:18.921 --> 01:33:22.387
This 79-year terror campaign

1490
01:33:22.522 --> 01:33:26.027
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1491
01:33:26.162 --> 01:33:27.964
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1492
01:33:28.099 --> 01:33:30.468
- Get out! Get out!
- Sorry. sir. we have...

1493
01:33:30.603 --> 01:33:32.639
Turn around and get out now!

1494
01:33:38.078 --> 01:33:40.944
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1495
01:33:41.079 --> 01:33:43.978
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1496
01:33:44.114 --> 01:33:46.617
- Her.
- Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1497
01:33:46.752 --> 01:33:48.286
- Him.
- Nathan Twinning.

1498
01:33:48.421 --> 01:33:49.821
Hugo's chief aide.

1499
01:33:49.956 --> 01:33:51.418
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1500
01:33:51.554 --> 01:33:53.253
Hang on.

1501
01:33:56.295 --> 01:34:00.766
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1502
01:34:02.100 --> 01:34:03.827
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1503
01:34:03.962 --> 01:34:06.669
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1504
01:34:15.383 --> 01:34:17.849
Sister Maura. Sister.

1505
01:34:26.127 --> 01:34:27.523
Jane?

1506
01:34:27.659 --> 01:34:29.088
Where are you. Jane?

1507
01:34:31.959 --> 01:34:33.491
Does God love us?

1508
01:34:33.626 --> 01:34:36.566
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1509
01:34:36.701 --> 01:34:40.401
Does he love only us?

1510
01:34:40.536 --> 01:34:42.741
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1511
01:34:42.877 --> 01:34:45.544
but do you think
it's possible that...

1512
01:34:45.679 --> 01:34:47.142
On Earth.

1513
01:34:48.446 --> 01:34:49.575
What?

1514
01:34:49.711 --> 01:34:51.213
Genesis.

1515
01:34:51.348 --> 01:34:56.019
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1516
01:35:05.129 --> 01:35:07.162
Do you think
there could be others?

1517
01:35:08.829 --> 01:35:10.863
Yes.

1518
01:35:10.998 --> 01:35:12.563
I would think so.

1519
01:35:12.698 --> 01:35:16.308
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1520
01:35:16.444 --> 01:35:20.472
yet save it only for us?

1521
01:35:21.541 --> 01:35:26.643
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1522
01:35:26.778 --> 01:35:30.317
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1523
01:35:32.153 --> 01:35:34.385
would that frighten you?

1524
01:35:34.521 --> 01:35:37.287
No. Why? Should it?

1525
01:35:37.423 --> 01:35:40.593
But what if it all collapsed?

1526
01:35:40.728 --> 01:35:43.059
For you and every other person
of faith in the world.

1527
01:35:43.194 --> 01:35:44.234
Then what?

1528
01:35:44.370 --> 01:35:45.534
Oh.

1529
01:35:45.670 --> 01:35:47.864
My dear. Jane.

1530
01:35:48.000 --> 01:35:52.910
I don't think that you ever
doubted your belief in God.

1531
01:35:53.046 --> 01:35:55.980
I think you lost your faith
in people.

1532
01:36:00.551 --> 01:36:03.988
They say you're paying because
you borrowed their phone?

1533
01:36:11.258 --> 01:36:12.893
Are you near the computer?

1534
01:36:13.029 --> 01:36:14.530
Yes.

1535
01:36:14.666 --> 01:36:16.897
What is KCXE?

1536
01:36:17.033 --> 01:36:19.597
Just those letters... KCXE.

1537
01:36:26.943 --> 01:36:28.873
Remember being a kid?

1538
01:36:29.008 --> 01:36:30.406
Sure.

1539
01:36:30.542 --> 01:36:32.951
Mostly stuff after I was ten.

1540
01:36:38.082 --> 01:36:42.092
Can you tell anything about me
from when I was small?

1541
01:37:01.074 --> 01:37:03.113
It's just a fox.

1542
01:37:16.631 --> 01:37:18.125
No. no. no. No!

1543
01:37:18.260 --> 01:37:21.030
- Stop! Stop!
- No. Daniel!

1544
01:37:23.068 --> 01:37:24.427
- Let's go. Come with us.
- Hold on.

1545
01:37:24.562 --> 01:37:26.603
- Hold on.
- Let's go.

1546
01:37:26.739 --> 01:37:28.334
I know him. I know him.

1547
01:37:28.470 --> 01:37:29.974
We just got to check you
real quick.

1548
01:37:30.110 --> 01:37:32.478
make sure nobody's in there
with you.

1549
01:37:39.947 --> 01:37:41.410
Clear.

1550
01:37:41.546 --> 01:37:43.580
All right. let's load up.

1551
01:37:43.716 --> 01:37:45.318
See. the thing about
fire trucks...

1552
01:37:45.454 --> 01:37:47.821
everyone gets the hell
out of your way.

1553
01:38:36.501 --> 01:38:38.268
I knew you'd make it.

1554
01:38:38.403 --> 01:38:39.873
I'm glad you knew.

1555
01:38:40.009 --> 01:38:41.607
Never a doubt.

1556
01:38:48.788 --> 01:38:50.451
Margaret.

1557
01:38:52.185 --> 01:38:53.619
Margaret.

1558
01:38:56.596 --> 01:38:57.964
Hello. Margaret.

1559
01:39:00.129 --> 01:39:02.325
Do you know who I am?

1560
01:39:02.461 --> 01:39:03.937
Of course. You're Hugo.

1561
01:39:06.770 --> 01:39:08.304
Nathan.

1562
01:39:09.709 --> 01:39:13.236
Chloe. Malik.

1563
01:39:13.371 --> 01:39:15.905
Jordan. Letisha.

1564
01:39:17.110 --> 01:39:18.912
Grace.

1565
01:39:19.047 --> 01:39:20.651
Hi. Terri.

1566
01:39:20.787 --> 01:39:22.714
Kaitlyn. That's Everett.

1567
01:39:50.279 --> 01:39:52.381
I think we got it mostly right.

1568
01:39:53.950 --> 01:39:55.313
Margaret.

1569
01:39:55.449 --> 01:39:57.987
Why won't you look at me?

1570
01:39:58.123 --> 01:39:59.617
Because you're-you're the guy.

1571
01:39:59.753 --> 01:40:01.852
You're the guy
who knows everything.

1572
01:40:03.528 --> 01:40:06.329
And I'm... and I'm not ready
to know everything.

1573
01:40:08.128 --> 01:40:11.561
Including. like. why-why my mom
and dad's entire goddamn house

1574
01:40:11.696 --> 01:40:13.038
is just sitting right there!

1575
01:40:13.174 --> 01:40:16.339
What is going on?
Why are you doing this?

1576
01:40:16.474 --> 01:40:18.371
That's where I grew up.
That's where I grew up.

1577
01:40:18.506 --> 01:40:21.674
This is my life.
This is my life.

1578
01:40:21.809 --> 01:40:24.007
And this matters...
what I want. who I am.

1579
01:40:24.142 --> 01:40:27.713
not who I am as you
or him or her. but as me.

1580
01:40:31.925 --> 01:40:33.820
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1581
01:40:33.956 --> 01:40:36.161
No. No.

1582
01:40:37.755 --> 01:40:40.396
I will not be anyone's religion.

1583
01:41:51.066 --> 01:41:52.501
My room.

1584
01:41:56.369 --> 01:41:58.243
Oh. my room.

1585
01:42:25.236 --> 01:42:27.739
Why would you build all of this?

1586
01:42:27.875 --> 01:42:30.308
To create a passage.

1587
01:42:32.375 --> 01:42:34.343
To return you to your experience

1588
01:42:34.478 --> 01:42:37.308
in the most familiar way
possible.

1589
01:42:37.443 --> 01:42:39.680
What experience?

1590
01:42:41.915 --> 01:42:44.113
The one you shared
with Margaret.

1591
01:42:45.891 --> 01:42:47.023
I shared?

1592
01:42:47.159 --> 01:42:49.428
I am not going back there.

1593
01:42:49.564 --> 01:42:51.187
- Hugo.
- How much do you remember about that night?

1594
01:42:51.322 --> 01:42:53.023
I don't remember.
and I don't want to remember.

1595
01:42:53.158 --> 01:42:54.726
and I don't want you
making me remember.

1596
01:42:54.861 --> 01:42:56.964
- Okay. Oh. my...
- Wait. Wait.

1597
01:42:57.099 --> 01:42:58.866
Wait.

1598
01:42:59.002 --> 01:43:00.836
Everything that happened to you
on the 23rd of February. 1996.

1599
01:43:00.972 --> 01:43:02.472
- is blocked.
- I don't want to know anything about it.

1600
01:43:02.607 --> 01:43:03.900
The only way for you
to know what's next

1601
01:43:04.036 --> 01:43:05.741
is to understand
what came before.

1602
01:43:05.877 --> 01:43:07.145
I don't want to talk about it.
I don't. Stop. stop. stop.

1603
01:43:07.281 --> 01:43:08.676
And then you'll know
your purpose.

1604
01:43:08.811 --> 01:43:10.005
Please don't make me.
I don't want to hear it.

1605
01:43:10.141 --> 01:43:10.981
You won't be
a passenger anymore.

1606
01:43:11.116 --> 01:43:12.713
I told you no!

1607
01:43:17.521 --> 01:43:20.817
You have the gift
but no control.

1608
01:43:20.952 --> 01:43:22.953
No understanding
of your purpose.

1609
01:43:23.088 --> 01:43:24.688
Not a clue as to
what your situation

1610
01:43:24.823 --> 01:43:27.022
will demand of you beyond today.

1611
01:43:27.158 --> 01:43:29.531
The only way for you
to acquire it

1612
01:43:29.666 --> 01:43:33.067
is to go back
to where it all began.

1613
01:43:33.202 --> 01:43:34.867
To go home.

1614
01:43:40.976 --> 01:43:45.008
And when you do. Margaret.
you'll know everything.

1615
01:43:45.144 --> 01:43:48.353
More than what was ever
humanly possible.

1616
01:44:09.603 --> 01:44:11.807
They gifted each of you.

1617
01:44:11.943 --> 01:44:14.903
Margaret. what was dormant
in you for most of your life

1618
01:44:15.039 --> 01:44:17.745
was activated only yesterday.

1619
01:44:18.744 --> 01:44:21.318
And yours. 15 years ago.

1620
01:44:21.454 --> 01:44:23.422
They gave you fluency
in the language

1621
01:44:23.557 --> 01:44:25.889
in which the book
of the universe is written:

1622
01:44:26.024 --> 01:44:27.758
mathematics.

1623
01:44:27.893 --> 01:44:31.354
Taught it to you. imbued it
so you could understand them.

1624
01:44:32.357 --> 01:44:36.467
And they imbued you
so you could understand us.

1625
01:44:38.731 --> 01:44:41.135
It's the two of you.

1626
01:44:42.838 --> 01:44:46.411
It's always been
just the two of you.

1627
01:45:08.661 --> 01:45:10.268
You can direct it

1628
01:45:10.404 --> 01:45:12.602
or feel where it wants
to take you.

1629
01:45:13.836 --> 01:45:15.802
It can find
what you're looking for.

1630
01:45:15.937 --> 01:45:18.805
It'll be an instrument
of your will.

1631
01:45:18.941 --> 01:45:21.314
But you must give yourself
over to it.

1632
01:45:22.614 --> 01:45:24.944
I'll find out
what's happening to me.

1633
01:45:27.447 --> 01:45:28.810
What?

1634
01:45:28.946 --> 01:45:30.481
It's gonna be okay.

1635
01:45:30.616 --> 01:45:32.116
I promise.

1636
01:45:49.308 --> 01:45:50.870
Whatever happens. Daniel.

1637
01:45:51.005 --> 01:45:53.038
- don't you let go.
- Don't you let go.

1638
01:45:56.246 --> 01:45:57.713
Margaret.

1639
01:46:00.179 --> 01:46:02.311
Look around the room
one more time.

1640
01:46:09.223 --> 01:46:12.693
You're a ten-year-old girl
asleep in your bed.

1641
01:46:12.829 --> 01:46:14.699
Something woke you up.
didn't it?

1642
01:46:14.835 --> 01:46:16.033
Yes.

1643
01:46:16.169 --> 01:46:17.865
So what did you do?

1644
01:46:18.862 --> 01:46:20.934
I sang my song.

1645
01:46:36.455 --> 01:46:40.024
♪ And away to his castle ♪

1646
01:46:40.159 --> 01:46:42.522
♪ We'll go ♪

1647
01:46:42.658 --> 01:46:46.360
♪ To be happy forever ♪

1648
01:46:46.495 --> 01:46:49.168
♪ I know ♪

1649
01:46:49.303 --> 01:46:53.263
♪ And the birds will sing. ♪

1650
01:47:03.742 --> 01:47:06.116
I can see them.

1651
01:47:06.251 --> 01:47:08.252
Right over there.

1652
01:47:08.388 --> 01:47:10.214
They're coming into the room.

1653
01:48:06.404 --> 01:48:08.277
No. no. no. don't go with them.

1654
01:48:08.413 --> 01:48:09.779
They're not animals.

1655
01:48:09.914 --> 01:48:11.841
Don't go with them.
They're not animals.

1656
01:48:11.977 --> 01:48:13.485
They're not animals!

1657
01:48:13.621 --> 01:48:15.213
- It's okay. It's okay.
- They're not.

1658
01:48:15.348 --> 01:48:19.184
They-they present as animals
to calm us.

1659
01:48:24.430 --> 01:48:27.060
When I walked through the glass.

1660
01:48:27.195 --> 01:48:31.130
it was like
this curtain of warm water.

1661
01:48:33.931 --> 01:48:36.338
And the snow...

1662
01:48:36.474 --> 01:48:39.710
was so warm on my feet.

1663
01:48:44.480 --> 01:48:46.442
The house.

1664
01:48:52.688 --> 01:48:55.286
"Hansel and Gretel."

1665
01:50:25.118 --> 01:50:26.784
Shh.

1666
01:50:32.622 --> 01:50:34.858
Hold my hand.

1667
01:52:11.620 --> 01:52:13.055
Whoa.

1668
01:52:15.019 --> 01:52:16.729
Whoa.

1669
01:52:54.433 --> 01:52:56.230
Hello. Hugo.

1670
01:52:59.598 --> 01:53:01.807
It's so nice
to finally know you.

1671
01:53:19.217 --> 01:53:20.820
They found us.

1672
01:53:23.293 --> 01:53:24.792
<i>Are they out front or out back?</i>

1673
01:53:24.928 --> 01:53:26.359
Most likely on all sides.

1674
01:53:26.494 --> 01:53:29.660
Okay. give me the. uh...
the-the-the thingy.

1675
01:53:29.795 --> 01:53:33.333
Thermal imaging showed
43 heat signatures inside here.

1676
01:53:33.469 --> 01:53:35.171
This whole area's
an industrial decay zone.

1677
01:53:35.307 --> 01:53:37.700
No other structure has
more than five people in it.

1678
01:53:45.311 --> 01:53:46.945
Hey.

1679
01:53:47.081 --> 01:53:49.448
Get on with it.

1680
01:54:33.800 --> 01:54:34.993
No one move.

1681
01:54:35.129 --> 01:54:37.369
No one make a sound.

1682
01:54:37.504 --> 01:54:38.937
They can't see us.

1683
01:54:42.476 --> 01:54:44.206
Give it to me.

1684
01:54:49.714 --> 01:54:51.477
This is not right.

1685
01:54:54.516 --> 01:54:58.187
They can't see us.
but they can see this.

1686
01:54:59.153 --> 01:55:01.851
We need to move now.

1687
01:55:01.986 --> 01:55:04.853
This is not gonna last long.
We got to go right now.

1688
01:55:15.205 --> 01:55:16.608
Look. They can't see me.

1689
01:55:16.743 --> 01:55:18.068
They can't see us. Let's go.

1690
01:55:18.204 --> 01:55:19.470
Quiet. quiet.

1691
01:55:19.605 --> 01:55:20.878
Through the back doors.
Any back door.

1692
01:55:21.014 --> 01:55:22.879
Go quiet. Go quiet.
Down the alley.

1693
01:55:23.014 --> 01:55:25.076
- Let's go. Let's go.
- Quiet.

1694
01:55:25.212 --> 01:55:27.980
Everybody. stop moving.

1695
01:55:36.123 --> 01:55:38.128
There. Look there.

1696
01:55:40.524 --> 01:55:42.164
Oh. God. I'm losing it.

1697
01:55:42.299 --> 01:55:43.968
I'm losing it.
You need to go faster.

1698
01:55:44.104 --> 01:55:45.770
- Get to the fire truck.
- I can't hold on.

1699
01:55:45.905 --> 01:55:47.065
- I can't hold...
- We got to go.

1700
01:55:47.200 --> 01:55:48.798
Stay on the light.

1701
01:55:51.911 --> 01:55:53.110
I can't hold on.

1702
01:56:03.415 --> 01:56:04.885
Let's go.

1703
01:56:08.094 --> 01:56:10.061
There. There.
Stay on the light.

1704
01:56:13.364 --> 01:56:15.627
- Stay on the light.
- The light! The light!

1705
01:56:43.130 --> 01:56:45.195
Hang on.
Grab ahold of something.

1706
01:57:06.414 --> 01:57:08.284
Which one do we follow?!

1707
01:57:09.584 --> 01:57:11.485
There's only one place
she's going.

1708
01:57:27.032 --> 01:57:28.534
SHEA Urgent measures are being

1709
01:57:28.670 --> 01:57:30.437
implemented across
the European Union.

1710
01:57:30.573 --> 01:57:32.205
where the Schengen Code
has been invoked.

1711
01:57:32.340 --> 01:57:33.711
closing all national borders...

1712
01:57:33.847 --> 01:57:36.708
- I...
- I know. I know.

1713
01:57:36.843 --> 01:57:38.942
For an imminent
inbound missile attack.

1714
01:57:39.077 --> 01:57:40.952
In North Korea.
a second breakaway faction

1715
01:57:41.088 --> 01:57:43.218
has announced
it has taken control

1716
01:57:43.354 --> 01:57:44.715
of as many as four
military bases

1717
01:57:44.851 --> 01:57:46.689
and confirm troop rollouts
from Pyongyang.

1718
01:57:46.825 --> 01:57:47.925
Where's Clay?

1719
01:57:48.060 --> 01:57:49.623
Taran Davies at the BBC

1720
01:57:49.758 --> 01:57:51.461
has a contact inside
the Korean Central News Agency.

1721
01:57:51.596 --> 01:57:54.260
the official news agency
of the North Korean government.

1722
01:57:54.396 --> 01:57:55.666
and had this to say earlier...

1723
01:57:55.802 --> 01:57:56.999
What are you doing here?

1724
01:57:57.135 --> 01:57:58.598
You should be in the hospital.

1725
01:58:00.199 --> 01:58:01.898
What...

1726
01:58:02.975 --> 01:58:04.572
Duncan is such a good boy.

1727
01:58:04.707 --> 01:58:07.772
and he needs you there tomorrow.
even if he can't say it.

1728
01:58:13.350 --> 01:58:15.050
I'm going on air
at the anchor desk

1729
01:58:15.185 --> 01:58:17.555
to deliver a special report.

1730
01:58:17.690 --> 01:58:20.458
O... o-okay.

1731
01:58:20.593 --> 01:58:21.850
Okay.

1732
01:58:21.986 --> 01:58:23.522
How do I get
to the control room?

1733
01:58:23.658 --> 01:58:25.126
I need to get
to the loading dock.

1734
01:58:25.262 --> 01:58:26.492
This is Daniel. This is Hugo.

1735
01:58:26.628 --> 01:58:28.056
- Clay. can you help us?
- Of course.

1736
01:58:28.191 --> 01:58:30.324
Uh. I don't know
what's happening. but come on.

1737
01:58:30.460 --> 01:58:32.061
Hailey.

1738
01:58:32.197 --> 01:58:34.772
The loading dock is
the second sign to the right.

1739
01:58:34.908 --> 01:58:36.574
What exactly is happening?

1740
01:58:36.709 --> 01:58:37.932
What's up?

1741
01:58:38.068 --> 01:58:39.238
Margaret's taking over
the anchor desk.

1742
01:58:39.374 --> 01:58:40.406
- What?
- Help her.

1743
01:58:40.541 --> 01:58:42.110
- Okay.
- The control room.

1744
01:58:42.246 --> 01:58:44.072
Why am I doing this? Come on.

1745
01:58:44.207 --> 01:58:45.777
The control room's upstairs.
Just follow me.

1746
01:58:48.120 --> 01:58:50.287
I called the police about him.

1747
01:58:51.589 --> 01:58:54.159
Maria and I moved out.
We're with my sister now.

1748
01:58:55.258 --> 01:58:57.192
- She's good.
- Good.

1749
01:58:57.327 --> 01:58:59.923
- Thank you.
- Of course.

1750
01:59:01.626 --> 01:59:03.091
Do you want makeup?

1751
01:59:04.098 --> 01:59:05.130
Yeah.

1752
01:59:17.375 --> 01:59:19.448
What's going on down there?
I had to hard-cut to commercial.

1753
01:59:19.583 --> 01:59:20.844
- Special report.
- What report?

1754
01:59:20.979 --> 01:59:22.643
- Who's this guy?
- He's gonna upload.

1755
01:59:22.779 --> 01:59:24.286
Do exactly what he says.

1756
01:59:24.422 --> 01:59:26.254
I'm putting it directly
on your server.

1757
01:59:26.389 --> 01:59:27.753
- This your coffee?
- Yes.

1758
01:59:28.822 --> 01:59:30.393
